          "text": "<teammate-message teammate_id=\"team-lead\">\nYou are implementing task group 3 (plus carry-over task 3.0) of the OpenSpec change `org-units` in /home/leon0399/Projects/llame (branch `stack/split-identity` — work in place, no worktree, NEVER push, NEVER touch GitHub). Phase 1 (DB invariants, RLS policies, triggers — commit 0a961e7) is done and accepted; you build the service/HTTP layer on top of it.\n\n## Required reading, in order, before any code\n1. openspec/changes/org-units/design.md — D5 is your endpoint table (authoritative); D1–D4 give the datastore semantics you're surfacing.\n2. openspec/changes/org-units/specs/org-units/spec.md + specs/org-memberships/spec.md — every HTTP-relevant scenario must have a test.\n3. openspec/changes/org-units/tasks.md — your scope: tasks 3.0, 3.1, 3.2, 3.3, 3.4. Nothing else.\n4. apps********S.md — REST/OpenAPI conventions (code-first, DTO + explicit response type per endpoint, PATCH not RPC verbs, ParseUUIDPipe), and the new \"app_rls (BYPASSRLS)\" section (dev DB sequence: `pnpm db:reset && pnpm db:migrate && pnpm db:provision-rls`; scripts/rls-test.sh self-provisions).\n5. Existing code: apps/api/src/identity/* (controller, service, repository, dto, all three integration specs), apps/api/src/db/schema/identity.ts, migration 0019 (read the policy/trigger comments — they define the error surface you must map).\n\n## Landmines from phase 1 you MUST design around\n- **Zero-rows DML under RLS USING**: an UPDATE/DELETE whose target row fails the USING policy does NOT error — it silently affects 0 rows. Every service update/delete MUST check the affected-row count and map 0 to the right status (404 if the caller can't even see the row, 403 if visible-but-not-permitted — where indistinguishable, prefer 404 to avoid an existence oracle; document the choice in code). A denied admin op must NEVER return success.\n- **SQLSTATE map** (extend the existing pgErrorCode pattern in identity.service.ts): 23505 → 409 duplicate membership; 23503 → 404 user/unit not found; 42501 → 403; 23514 (path integrity) → 409 \"concurrent reorganization, retry\"; OW001 (last-owner trigger) → 409 \"transfer ownership first\". The last two are custom outcomes from migration 0019's triggers.\n- Repository `grant()` deliberately has no RETURNING (SELECT policy hides the grantee's row from the granter) — same applies to any new INSERT you add.\n- Move-to-root semantics: RLS's update WITH CHECK requires admin-tier on the NEW path; for a to-root move the new path is the unit's own id, so the mover needs owner/admin membership ON THE UNIT ITSELF (not just an ancestor). That's the designed behavior — test it, don't fight it.\n\n## Tasks\n- **3.0 (carry-over F4)**: in identity-repository.ts — `findByIdInLockedTree` gets a lock-then-verify loop (after locking the observed tree root, re-read; if the first path segment changed, lock the new root too and re-read; repeat until stable). `move()` re-reads `newParent` under the held locks and derives `newPrefix` AND the into-own-subtree guard from the re-reads, never caller-supplied rows.\n- **3.1 Service methods** (all inside `tenantDb.runAs`, following the existing style): `getOrgUnit`, `renameOrgUnit`, `updateOrgUnitSettings` (or fold into one `updateOrgUnit` matching PATCH semantics), `moveOrgUnit` (incl. to-root — repository needs a to-root variant: path rebases onto the unit's own id, parent_id NULL, old tree root locked), `deleteOrgUnit`, `listMemberships` (roster), `changeMembershipRole`, `revokeMembership` (self-leave and admin-revoke), and expose `resolveRole` for the /me endpoint.\n- **3.2 Controller + DTOs** per design.md D5's table exactly: `GET /api/v1/org-units/:id`, `PATCH /api/v1/org-units/:id` ({name?, settings?, parentId?} — parentId present-and-null promotes to root; use a DTO shape that distinguishes absent from null), `DELETE /api/v1/org-units/:id`, `GET/POST /:id/memberships` (POST widens grantable roles to all SPEC roles EXCEPT service_account — including owner, which RLS gates to owner-tier), `PATCH/DELETE /:id/memberships/:userId`, `GET /:id/memberships/me` (effective role: role, viaOrgUnitId, inherited). Full OpenAPI annotations; regenerate openapi.json (check how the repo generates it — there's an existing script/flow since apps/api/openapi.json is committed).\n- **3.3 Integration tests** (extend the existing identity spec files / patterns): every endpoint happy path + 403/404/409 semantics per the spec scenarios; move-into-own-subtree → 422; last-owner leave → 409; owner transfer via grant+self-demote flow works end-to-end; roster invisible cross-tenant over HTTP; settings PATCH round-trips.\n- **3.4** Full gates green: `pnpm --filter api lint`, `typecheck`, `test`, `db:check`, and `bash apps/api/scripts/rls-test.sh` (known flake: if red, re-run serially --runInBand before treating as regression).\n\n## Working agreements\n- Mark tasks.md checkboxes as you complete each task.\n- ONE commit for the group: `feat(api): org-units service + RESTful admin surface (org-units 3.x)` + `Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>`. Never push; never git reset --hard/clean.\n- Match existing style (identity.service.ts / identity.controller.ts are the bar). Minimum code; no speculative abstraction; no API client generation.\n- Work autonomously end-to-end. Message me mid-work ONLY for a genuine design contradiction you cannot resolve; everything else: decide, note it in the final report.\n- Final report: per-task summary, commit SHA, every gate's real outcome, all decisions/deviations, anything deferred.\n</teammate-message>",
